  "title": "Community Models Alpha is live",
  "summary": "We shipped 3D generation, opened the gates for community-hosted models, and wired up OAuth 2.1.\n\nYou can now plug your own models into our infrastructure and charge for them. We shipped the Community Models Alpha, complete with a `/account/my-models` API, CLI tools, and auto-deactivation for unstable endpoints. The first batch of community creators has been allowlisted and is already serving traffic.\n\nPixels are great, but sometimes you need depth. We added a `/3d/{prompt}` endpoint powered by Trellis 2 and Rodin 2.5 for instant GLB generation. On the 2D front, we added Claude Sonnet 5, restored Claude Fable 5, and introduced a half-price Nano Banana 2 Lite model.\n\nWe shipped OAuth 2.1 with PKCE, meaning you can now build apps with secure, delegated API access without passing raw keys around. We also routed Flux to a self-hosted Vast.ai RTX 5090 pool, dropping median generation times to 2.25s, and added a real-time `/v1/models/status` endpoint.\n\nThe 'App listed on Pollinations' quest is now live and claimable. We added CLI commands (`polli quests mine`) to track your earned Pollen, and wired up declarative billing adjustments so Perplexity search fees and Gemini grounding costs are transparently itemized.",
